OCTOBER TERM, 1767. Hutchins vs. Brown. Orb bred, that the following amendment be made in the return of an attachment issued on the 2d of January *4991761, out of tins court, by Thomas E. Hutchins, against the goods and chattels, lands and tenements, of John Brown, of Queen-Anne’s county, to wit. “The execution of the within writ appeal’s by the schedule thereto annexed.

“So answers Jos. Nichobson, Shff. Q. A. C.” aud the “Cepi Corpus” to be struck out.
